title: KILLING EVE - S1 Ep 7 & 8
body:
Listen, loved this danger-flirty glamorous killer/plucky investigator murdermance, obviously, of course I love the stylish morbid sharp grim hilarious bloody queer New Cold War spy thriller filled with WEIRDO WOMEN who are always messing things up and being very good at their jobs and eating snacks. BRAVA.

Y’know I’d told a friend back in the early episodes that this was well-plotted, but I think what I actually meant is that it was well-paced. I tend to get distracted by spy plots because I LOVE THEM ALL THE TIME FOREVER, but at the end here I can see that within the (superior) sub-set “spy plot”, this is not exactly a premier example. However, while loose, it strides along at such a nice pace! This show is constantly entertaining, sometimes thrilling, always nice and fun to watch. The humor is essential to this, and wonderful. And that the story is peopled by the kind of characters it is. God they’re all so GREAT.

Season 1, Episode 7 - ‘I Don’t Want To Be Free’

Eve…you’re supposed to be secret service. how are you sooo dense about some things, but so brilliant about others.. Truly, people Be Complicated

mmm love when the game turns on you and now you’re on thin ice in like, the entire damn country #SPY STORIES

I think Konstantin told Carolyn to stop looking for Villanelle last night, I think that’s the flow here

Kenny’s gotten little personal growth plot just for him! hope Elena does too, we have like an episode and a half left

okay what the fuck is up with this Inga!

[points] same hair! same hair!!!

shit, maybe Oksana just murdered Anna’s husband out of jealousy, nothing more! man, I did it again, still expecting assault and there not being any!

yeah sure I mean, why not go over to her place and get cake

god all her different deployed smiles are so good

loves it, loves carnage

you’re no Konstantin [frowns]

Villanelle: “Are you always like this?”
Anton: “Like what?”
Villanelle: [okay]
Villanelle: [shoots him in the head]

nnNOOOOO not handler dad! don’t do it I still like him!

oh. oh that is a lot of carefully organized letters

I see why Oksana loved her. but also holy heck my girl she was your teacher.

Eve is so interesting, because as mentioned before, very socially dense, but she also has incredibly good atypical instincts for what do to in certain social situations to get the right outcomes.

really good how Konstantin has become like, the disgruntled silver bear that everyone loves. including ME.

Konstantin this cute house!

#sausages theme

ohhhh, this is her cache! she knows Anna will keep the jacket and never wear it, leaving this money and passport safe in her house! CLEVER, VILL

listen I’m obsessed with this little white house!!

“Why did they want me in there? I’m amazing.” girl I can’t breathe you ARE amazing

what the fuck why is he telling her every absurd sweet thing she’d want to hear, omg Konstantin are you for reals!

loooooolllll no he was not for reals

flipping her off, with dignity, from his speedboat. still love you both!!

buddy she’s probably gonna kill your family now though

Anna is really lovely. but also as much of a weirdo as every other woman in this, so, great job all around show!

Eve & Kenny is such a combo

aaaahhhh!!!!

this show has so many TWISTS

Season 1, Episode 8 - ‘God, I’m Tired’

this…..is fully incredible, bless this scene, bless them both just, YELLING. “My dad is going to kill you in the face!” “No I’m going to kill your dad in the face!”

Eve just called Villanelle her girlfriend. it was kinda a joke? but it was not a laugh line, it was a closer line, and there is a difference!

just sitting in this bench munching fast food

“Why is your English so good.”
“Language is information.”
Both: “And information is everything.”

Jodie Comer has spent the majority of this show with injuries on her face

Konstantin just assured them his daughter is so annoying, and then teared up. DAD.

they’re both SO ANNOYING, I looove them

S H R I E K ! ! !  !

her giant eyes so full of dark tears!

twinning: Eve idly flipping that same glove compartment handle Villanelle was

Eve: “I think the best sex we ever had was on that chair.”
Kid: “Oh god.”
Me: [squawk]

whooooooaa

the reason why Eve is such a great character is because she constantly makes interesting pairs. her and Konstantin? hilarious! they’re both currently laughing like suspicious unhinged maniacs, which they are, driving through the rainy streets of Moscow after someone who would totally kill them like “fuck it”

meanwhile Irina and Villanelle are ANOTHER great pair

of course you like her

will he live??? I DIDN’T GET TO KEEP BILL

I do not get to keep Konstantin

yes Elena, yeessss. I miss you.

of course it has to end in Paris, this show’s most ~aesthetic~ location

lol, yes Eve would like to see your Records

…..old French neighbor just *literally* described Konstantin as a nice-looking grey haired [growls like a bear], so, Point Wellntruly

Villanelle’s apartment is just…top tier. everything. golden fish bath faucet? this deco mirror? stop it.

I love the strings of this song kicking in while I love that her fridge is stocked with nothing but champaaaaaagne

yeah get it out, raaaaage

Eve: “I think about you all the time. I think about what you’re wearing, and what you’re doing, and who you’re doing it with.”
Villanelle: “I think about you too. I mean I masturbate about you a lot.”
listen Hannibal never did This

pls omg just nap together, that would be so weird and intimate and perfect

this whole show has narrowed to these two exhausted women lying on a bed I am breathless

what Eve omg!!!!!!

NO SHE’S MY MURDERBABY

how is this so tense and shocking and moving and also still sharply funny!!!!!

Eve you fucking lunatic! Villanelle YOU fucking lunatic!

of course though, of course, how else are you guys gonna love each other besides…this. messy, BLOODY, simultaneously very effective and fail-boating everywhere.

LIVE, LIVE MY TERRIBLE DARLING

alright see you peeps in Season 2

summary: From fridging to nagging husbands: How Killing Eve upturns sexist cliches
title: From fridging to nagging husbands: How Killing Eve upturns sexist cliches
excerpt: The glorious cat-and-mouse thriller subverted decades of spy-thriller tropes. Here are its archetype-slaying moments
description: Picking apart the details of Killing Eve is probably the most fun you can have in 2018. (Which, considering this year, is slightly damning it with faint praise.) There’s so much to love about Phoebe Waller-Bridge’s glorious cat-and-mouse thriller, from its preposterous, hysterical tone to its triptych of female leads, all of whom could shatter the Bechdel test with a single withering look. Sandra Oh’s Fargo-esque Eve Polastri. Jodie Comer’s Villanelle, who is everything you would expect a psychopath dreamed up by the creator of Fleabag to be. And Fiona Shaw’s Carolyn Martens, who nails lines never before placed in the mouth of a possible double agent. Like: “I once saw a rat drink from a can of Coke there. Two hands. Extraordinary.”
